HEADWORD: Terrel
<hw>Ter"rel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>terrella</ets>, from L. <ets>terra</ets> the earth.]</ety> <def>A
spherical magnet so placed that its poles, equator, etc., correspond to
those of the earth.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chambers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

